Description: Bongo Penguin applet for the COSMIC desktop
 A Bongo-Cat-style applet for the COSMIC desktop environment (Pop!_OS),
 starring Tux the Linux penguin. The penguin sits in the COSMIC panel or
 dock and drums its flippers in response to every keystroke and mouse
 click — system-wide, including games under Proton, exclusive fullscreen,
 and native Wayland applications.
 .
 Includes a live keystroke counter that survives reboots, encrypted with
 AES-256-GCM and bound to the machine's /etc/machine-id so counts can't
 be trivially copied between installations.
